WEBVTT

00:00.960 --> 00:03.170
[♪♪♪]

00:04.755 --> 00:07.716
I can't believe we're getting
married in only three days.

00:07.716 --> 00:09.677
And there's still
so much to be done.

00:09.677 --> 00:12.596
Oh, we don't have to check off
every last item on that list.

00:12.596 --> 00:14.306
It'll still be
a beautiful wedding.

00:14.306 --> 00:16.809
Well, some of these items
aren't exactly optional.

00:16.809 --> 00:19.436
We still don't have a pastor.
No word from Frank yet?

00:19.436 --> 00:22.189
No. I wrote to him
a few days ago,

00:22.189 --> 00:23.524
but I haven't heard back.

00:23.524 --> 00:25.860
I even sent a telegram to
Children's Hospital,

00:25.860 --> 00:28.487
in Cape Fullerton,
where he's been volunteering.

00:28.487 --> 00:31.323
He's been gone so long.
I hope he's okay.

00:31.323 --> 00:33.283
And you miss him.

00:34.493 --> 00:35.828
I do.

00:35.828 --> 00:38.664
But not to worry,
the wedding must go on,

00:38.664 --> 00:41.000
even if I have to perform
the ceremony myself.

00:41.000 --> 00:42.626
You can do that?

00:42.626 --> 00:45.004
As mayor of the town,
I have the legal authority.

00:45.004 --> 00:46.463
[CHUCKLES]
Then we're covered.

00:46.463 --> 00:49.008
But I have faith
Frank will be here.

00:49.800 --> 00:51.760
I hope you're right.

00:57.182 --> 00:58.183
Sheriff?

00:58.183 --> 00:59.935
Have you seen Jack?

00:59.935 --> 01:01.729
He's out.
Something the matter?

01:01.729 --> 01:03.271
I've got a telegram for him.

01:03.271 --> 01:04.940
Mountie headquarters.

01:04.940 --> 01:07.192
[♪♪♪]

01:07.192 --> 01:09.194
Is that going
to affect the wedding?

01:09.862 --> 01:10.905
No.

01:12.239 --> 01:13.949
When are you gonna
give it to him?

01:13.949 --> 01:15.993
I'll see that he gets it.

01:17.411 --> 01:19.329
Yes.

01:22.541 --> 01:24.418
[ELIZABETH &amp; JACK LAUGHING]

01:24.418 --> 01:26.628
[♪♪♪]

01:27.379 --> 01:29.297
Whoo!

01:33.301 --> 01:34.887
Whoa, Sergeant.

01:34.887 --> 01:36.555
Why are we stopping?

01:36.555 --> 01:38.807
I just thought
of something.

01:40.768 --> 01:42.519
What is it?

01:43.979 --> 01:45.313
Hmm.

01:47.232 --> 01:48.650
What was that for?

01:48.650 --> 01:51.779
I wanted to kiss
Miss Elizabeth Thatcher

01:51.779 --> 01:54.406
before she becomes
Mrs. Jack Thornton.

01:56.075 --> 01:58.159
I can't wait.

02:01.872 --> 02:04.083
[♪♪♪]

02:22.017 --> 02:26.271
ELIZABETH:
If seven multiplied by
six equals 42,

02:26.271 --> 02:30.818
then what do we get when
we multiply seven by seven?

02:30.818 --> 02:32.527
[ALL WHISPERING
INDISTINCTLY]

02:34.237 --> 02:37.240
It appears something else has
captured your attention today.

02:37.240 --> 02:39.284
Miss Thatcher,
when are you gonna start

02:39.284 --> 02:41.411
decorating in here
for your wedding?

02:41.411 --> 02:42.704
[SIGHS]

02:42.704 --> 02:44.581
Tomorrow morning,
bright and early.

02:44.581 --> 02:45.833
Maybe we could help.

02:45.833 --> 02:47.292
Oh,
that's very generous,

02:47.292 --> 02:49.711
but do you wanna spend
your Saturday at school?

02:49.711 --> 02:50.712
I meant today.

02:50.712 --> 02:52.255
We could start
decorating now.

02:52.255 --> 02:53.841
Could we?

02:53.841 --> 02:55.342
[CHUCKLES]
Are you sure

02:55.342 --> 02:57.511
you'd rather decorate
than study mathematics?

02:57.511 --> 02:59.429
[IN UNISON]
Yeah!

02:59.429 --> 03:01.556
[LAUGHS]
All right.

03:01.556 --> 03:03.809
Well, since
it's a special occasion,

03:03.809 --> 03:06.520
I'm willing to make an exception
just this once.

03:06.520 --> 03:08.480
[IN UNISON]
Yay!

03:08.480 --> 03:10.189
Now, I'm going to need
two groups:

03:10.189 --> 03:11.942
one to start
decorating the pews,

03:11.942 --> 03:15.194
and the older children can start
taking down the school posters.

03:15.194 --> 03:17.531
Let's get started.

03:17.531 --> 03:19.950
[CHILDREN CHATTERING]
[CHUCKLES]

03:19.950 --> 03:22.161
[♪♪♪]

03:23.286 --> 03:24.955
I'm wondering
if we shouldn't

03:24.955 --> 03:27.082
raise this
just a little...

03:27.082 --> 03:28.917
Clara, I think
you're right.

03:28.917 --> 03:31.252
Elizabeth is,
shall we say,

03:31.252 --> 03:33.130
quite modest.
[CHUCKLES]

03:33.130 --> 03:35.883
It's such a beautiful
design, Rosemary.

03:35.883 --> 03:38.426
[CHUCKLES]
Oh, Clara! This has
been a group effort

03:38.426 --> 03:42.056
between you, me, and Dottie,
from start to finish.

03:42.056 --> 03:43.515
Oh, thank goodness.

03:43.515 --> 03:44.933
Wonderful!
You got more silk.

03:44.933 --> 03:46.560
[SIGHS]
It wasn't easy.

03:46.560 --> 03:49.396
Oh, what kind of heartless
creature could possibly

03:49.396 --> 03:52.399
deny you the material necessary
to finish a wedding dress?

03:52.399 --> 03:54.317
A creature who needs
to make a living.

03:54.317 --> 03:56.195
Since we're short on cash,
I had to do

03:56.195 --> 03:58.363
a little bartering
with our Buxton supplier.

03:58.363 --> 04:00.782
We owe him a bolt of cotton
on our next visit.

04:02.159 --> 04:03.618
[WOMEN YELP]
Jack!

04:03.618 --> 04:05.829
[♪♪♪]

04:07.748 --> 04:09.666
Oh!
JACK: Ladies.

04:09.666 --> 04:11.001
You two should know better

04:11.001 --> 04:12.920
than to come in here
without warning.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.295
What is all the fuss?

04:14.295 --> 04:17.507
[SCOFFS]
The groom
absolutely cannot see

04:17.507 --> 04:19.927
the bride's dress
before it is on the bride,

04:19.927 --> 04:21.887
in the church,
at the wedding.

04:21.887 --> 04:23.972
I didn't know that.
Neither did I.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.057
[SCOFFS]
Men.

04:25.057 --> 04:26.975
You must be here
for the suits.

04:26.975 --> 04:28.518
I'm sorry,
but they're not ready.

04:28.518 --> 04:30.854
ROSEMARY:
Clara has been working
day and night

04:30.854 --> 04:34.149
on Elizabeth's wedding dress. It
takes priority above all else.

04:34.149 --> 04:35.609
So we're learning.

04:35.609 --> 04:37.152
Any idea when
they'll be done?

04:37.152 --> 04:38.946
Uh, by tomorrow morning.

04:38.946 --> 04:41.322
Okay, great. We should
probably get going then.

04:41.322 --> 04:43.033
Well, unless
you want us to stay.

04:43.033 --> 04:44.659
[IN UNISON]
Go!

04:44.659 --> 04:46.161
They want us to leave.

04:46.161 --> 04:47.829
Jack, what are
you doing here?

04:47.829 --> 04:49.539
Actually,
we were just leaving.

04:49.539 --> 04:51.499
Ladies,
we'll leave you to it.

04:51.499 --> 04:52.793
Good luck.

04:52.793 --> 04:55.170
[SIGHS]
That was too close.

04:55.170 --> 04:56.838
Jack almost saw
your wedding dress.

04:56.838 --> 04:59.049
He didn't.
Thank goodness.

04:59.049 --> 05:00.217
[ROSEMARY CHUCKLES]

05:00.217 --> 05:01.384
I'm glad to hear it.

05:01.384 --> 05:03.470
But, Elizabeth,
your fitting

05:03.470 --> 05:05.013
isn't for another hour
or so.

05:05.013 --> 05:07.224
I gave the children
a break from decorating,

05:07.224 --> 05:09.559
so I thought I'd stop by
while I had the chance.

05:09.559 --> 05:12.271
Well, I'm sorry, but we aren't
ready for your fitting.

05:12.271 --> 05:14.314
I need that extra hour.
That's all right.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.233
I'd like to keep an eye
on the children.

05:16.233 --> 05:18.819
Is there a way we can do
the fitting at the school?

05:18.819 --> 05:21.696
I can make that work.
We'll bring the dress to you.

05:21.696 --> 05:23.907
[♪♪♪]

05:25.450 --> 05:26.660
How long are you gone?

05:26.660 --> 05:28.287
A day, a day
and a half, tops.

05:28.287 --> 05:29.913
There's a Mountie
that needs help

05:29.913 --> 05:32.499
escorting a prisoner
to Cape Fullerton.

05:32.499 --> 05:33.750
This is for Jack.

05:33.750 --> 05:35.627
Jack's not gonna be
escorting anybody

05:35.627 --> 05:37.087
but Elizabeth
down the aisle.

05:37.087 --> 05:39.006
Be careful, Bill.

05:39.006 --> 05:40.674
JACK:
Afternoon.

05:40.674 --> 05:42.301
Hope I'm not
interrupting anything.

05:42.301 --> 05:44.303
No.
No, uh...

05:44.303 --> 05:46.387
Just boring town business.

05:49.057 --> 05:50.558
Okay.

05:50.558 --> 05:51.726
Headed somewhere?

05:51.726 --> 05:53.854
Just more
boring town business.

05:53.854 --> 05:56.064
Well, you lead quite the life.

05:56.064 --> 05:58.859
Yeah, I'll be back in plenty
of time for the wedding.

05:58.859 --> 06:01.444
You'd better, or I'm gonna come
and hunt you down.

06:01.444 --> 06:02.988
You got it.

06:04.823 --> 06:06.491
[HORN HONKS]

06:07.492 --> 06:09.328
[HORN HONKS AGAIN]

06:10.078 --> 06:11.496
Tom?

06:12.206 --> 06:13.248
Hey, big brother.

06:13.248 --> 06:14.541
Wo-- I can't believe it.

06:14.541 --> 06:16.918
You didn't think I'd miss
your wedding?

06:16.918 --> 06:19.171
How'd you know?
I didn't have your address.

06:19.171 --> 06:20.630
Business keeps me on the road,

06:20.630 --> 06:22.507
but Mom cabled me
about your wedding.

06:22.507 --> 06:24.259
If there's any way she could've,
she'd have been here.

06:24.259 --> 06:26.469
Is she gonna be okay?
She wrenched her back

06:26.469 --> 06:27.971
being thrown off that horse.

06:27.971 --> 06:30.057
But you know Mom:
she's down, but never out.

06:30.057 --> 06:32.684
Right. Well,
I'm just glad to see you.

06:32.684 --> 06:35.103
This whole new you.
I represent a tire company.

06:35.103 --> 06:37.064
Let me tell you,
the future's in rubber.

06:37.064 --> 06:38.648
Wow, okay.

06:38.648 --> 06:41.026
I'm gonna buy you a drink.

06:42.861 --> 06:45.739
Actually, better yet,
you buy me one.

06:45.739 --> 06:47.115
[CHUCKLES]

06:47.699 --> 06:48.950
Hello.

06:48.950 --> 06:50.744
I'm here to buy
some candy, please.

06:50.744 --> 06:51.912
Three cents.
I will have

06:51.912 --> 06:53.872
the red ones
and the green ones.

06:55.332 --> 06:57.918
I've never lit candles
for a wedding before, have you?

06:57.918 --> 06:59.627
How hard can it be?
When it's time,

06:59.627 --> 07:01.420
we step forward,
light the candles.

07:01.420 --> 07:03.048
What if we do something wrong?

07:03.048 --> 07:04.883
Everybody's gonna be
watching us.

07:04.883 --> 07:08.469
Maybe you should rehearse it,
like we do for our school plays.

07:08.469 --> 07:09.804
Rehearse where?

07:09.804 --> 07:12.473
The school.
The side door is usually open.

07:12.473 --> 07:13.641
That's a good idea.

07:13.641 --> 07:15.435
Did Miss Thatcher
give you a job?

07:15.435 --> 07:17.312
She sure did.
I'm an usher.

07:17.312 --> 07:18.813
What's an usher do?

07:18.813 --> 07:21.566
I don't really know,
but I bet it's important.

07:22.776 --> 07:23.735
Thank you.

07:23.735 --> 07:26.238
[IN UNISON]
Thank you.

07:28.698 --> 07:30.909
[♪♪♪]

07:38.292 --> 07:40.335
Hello?

07:43.880 --> 07:45.006
Hello?

07:45.006 --> 07:46.466
MOUNTIE:
Identify yourself.

07:48.718 --> 07:51.012
Sheriff Bill Avery,
from Hope Valley.

07:51.012 --> 07:53.598
I'm here to escort
your prisoner to jail.

07:56.059 --> 07:57.311
What's the problem?

07:57.311 --> 08:00.105
No problem.
Just being careful.

08:00.105 --> 08:02.023
This is Joe Yancy.
Ever heard of him?

08:02.023 --> 08:04.567
BILL:
Head of the Yancy Gang,
out of Waterston.

08:04.567 --> 08:05.986
Let's go.

08:05.986 --> 08:07.446
Right now?

08:07.446 --> 08:09.739
Wanna get to Cape Fullerton
before nightfall.

08:09.739 --> 08:10.824
We leave now.

08:17.372 --> 08:19.582
[♪♪♪]

08:21.793 --> 08:23.295
Get him back inside.

08:23.295 --> 08:24.921
They're onto you!

08:24.921 --> 08:26.465
[GUNSHOTS]

08:31.594 --> 08:33.096
[NEIGHS]

08:37.225 --> 08:38.685
[GUNSHOT]

08:40.020 --> 08:42.563
That fear on your face
suits you, Sheriff.

08:47.027 --> 08:49.070
[CLICKING]

08:50.030 --> 08:50.989
They cut the wire.

08:50.989 --> 08:52.782
[SIGHS]
Now what?

09:02.583 --> 09:03.835
Thank you.

09:03.835 --> 09:06.046
[GASPS]
Rosemary.

09:06.046 --> 09:07.255
Julie.

09:07.255 --> 09:09.757
Oh, welcome.

09:09.757 --> 09:11.926
Oh, I'm so glad
that you made it.

09:11.926 --> 09:12.969
I wouldn't miss it.

09:12.969 --> 09:14.471
How's everything coming along?

09:14.471 --> 09:16.014
Well, I can honestly say,

09:16.014 --> 09:18.475
I've never been
so busy in my entire life,

09:18.475 --> 09:20.435
but it's a labor of love.

09:20.435 --> 09:22.770
On that note,
I really need to run.

09:22.770 --> 09:24.439
[SPUTTERING]
Oh, ah--

09:25.648 --> 09:27.526
ABIGAIL:
The hors d'oeuvres
are ready,

09:27.526 --> 09:29.486
now we move on
to choice of entrées--

09:29.486 --> 09:31.029
Chicken or prime rib,

09:31.029 --> 09:33.532
with sides of duchess potatoes,
candied carrots,

09:33.532 --> 09:35.742
gratin of broccoli,
and green beans almandine.

09:35.742 --> 09:38.703
That all sounds delicious,
but do we need that many sides?

09:38.703 --> 09:39.954
If we dropped a few,

09:39.954 --> 09:42.123
you might get to
enjoy the reception.

09:42.123 --> 09:44.209
Well, ordinarily,
I'd argue with you,

09:44.209 --> 09:45.877
but I'm a little shorthanded.

09:45.877 --> 09:47.712
Bill was helping out,
until he had to

09:47.712 --> 09:49.256
leave town
on Mountie business.

09:49.256 --> 09:51.716
Why is Bill doing Mountie
business, and not Jack?

09:51.716 --> 09:54.302
Well, there is always
a possibility of danger.

09:54.302 --> 09:57.180
He didn't want Jack to leave
town just before the wedding.

09:57.180 --> 09:59.307
Aw. And he didn't
want him to know.

10:00.183 --> 10:01.560
That's really kind of him.

10:01.560 --> 10:03.270
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

10:03.270 --> 10:04.938
Hello!

10:04.938 --> 10:06.981
[GASPS]
Julie!

10:06.981 --> 10:09.484
[LAUGHS]

10:09.484 --> 10:11.152
[BOTH SIGHING]

10:11.152 --> 10:13.071
I hear the whole town
is at work

10:13.071 --> 10:14.989
getting ready
for your wedding.

10:14.989 --> 10:17.492
[GASPS]
Good to see you,
Abigail.

10:17.492 --> 10:19.035
Good to see you,
too, Julie.

10:19.035 --> 10:21.704
Elizabeth tells me
your mother's still in London?

10:21.704 --> 10:23.664
Caring for our sister
and her new baby.

10:23.664 --> 10:25.792
I'm not sure which one
demands more attention.

10:25.792 --> 10:28.253
ELIZABETH:
It's so sad they'll miss
the ceremony.

10:28.253 --> 10:31.214
It is, but Father
will be here tomorrow.

10:31.214 --> 10:33.592
So how can I help?

10:33.592 --> 10:36.595
Well, they could use help
decorating the church.

10:36.595 --> 10:38.012
I'm on my way.

10:38.012 --> 10:39.806
[BOTH GIGGLE]

10:39.806 --> 10:41.141
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

10:41.141 --> 10:42.559
This is really happening.

10:42.559 --> 10:43.560
[BOTH GIGGLE]

10:43.560 --> 10:45.061
It is.

10:45.686 --> 10:47.606
[♪♪♪]

10:50.358 --> 10:51.985
THUG:
Lawmen!

10:51.985 --> 10:54.613
You hearing me?

10:55.489 --> 10:56.906
Hey! Lawmen!

10:56.906 --> 11:00.118
They can hear ya, Wade!
They're just cowards!

11:00.118 --> 11:01.536
[LAUGHS]

11:01.536 --> 11:04.498
I need to shut you up.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.751
[GUNFIRE]

11:14.841 --> 11:16.259
[PANTING]

11:16.259 --> 11:18.345
[PANTING]

11:25.352 --> 11:26.894
What are those?

11:28.605 --> 11:30.689
This is why we can't wait
for the patrol.

11:30.689 --> 11:33.067
We got to get out of here
as soon as possible.

11:37.364 --> 11:40.283
[♪♪♪]

11:40.283 --> 11:43.244
JULIE:
So the curtains are going to be
hung at every window,

11:43.244 --> 11:46.039
and then the flowers can be
put at the end of every pew.

11:46.039 --> 11:48.124
Thank you, ladies.
Excuse me, miss.

11:48.124 --> 11:50.126
Do you know where
I might put these c--?

11:50.126 --> 11:51.503
Julie.

11:51.503 --> 11:52.629
Tom.

11:52.629 --> 11:54.381
I wondered
if you'd be here.

11:54.381 --> 11:56.216
You look...

11:56.216 --> 11:57.592
different.

11:57.592 --> 12:00.261
Heh. Good "different"
or bad "different"?

12:00.261 --> 12:01.971
Dignified "different."

12:01.971 --> 12:04.140
Mm! Thank you.

12:04.140 --> 12:05.559
You look, um...

12:05.559 --> 12:07.477
happy.

12:07.477 --> 12:11.314
The last time I saw you,
you weren't.

12:11.314 --> 12:14.234
I needed to find my place
in the world.

12:14.234 --> 12:15.818
And I have.

12:15.818 --> 12:17.571
I enrolled in art school.

12:17.571 --> 12:20.156
Well, you always did
have an artistic flare.

12:20.156 --> 12:22.200
And you were always
full of surprises.

12:22.200 --> 12:24.327
[LAUGHS]

12:26.621 --> 12:28.623
Um...

12:28.623 --> 12:31.626
So did you bring a date
for the wedding?

12:31.626 --> 12:33.712
No. No.

12:35.714 --> 12:37.257
Oh.

12:37.924 --> 12:40.301
[SNORTING]

12:40.301 --> 12:42.053
[♪♪♪]

13:01.531 --> 13:03.617
[CREAKING]

13:05.410 --> 13:07.245
You know where this goes?

13:07.245 --> 13:09.038
I didn't even know
that was there.

13:20.759 --> 13:22.719
We make our move
after it turns dark.

13:26.598 --> 13:28.475
ABIGAIL:
Thank you for all your help.

13:28.475 --> 13:29.559
CARSON:
You're welcome.

13:29.559 --> 13:31.144
I like being
in the kitchen.

13:31.144 --> 13:33.854
Plus, you have an army
of guests to feed.

13:33.854 --> 13:35.148
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

13:35.148 --> 13:37.108
So, what do you
think of the menu?

13:37.108 --> 13:39.694
Well, I think
it's ambitious.

13:39.694 --> 13:41.321
Pulling out
all the stops.

13:41.321 --> 13:44.365
Well, it's a big day,
and I can hardly wait.

13:44.365 --> 13:45.700
Me either.

13:45.700 --> 13:46.951
[GASPS]

13:46.951 --> 13:48.620
Frank!

13:50.288 --> 13:51.372
Hi, Carson.

13:51.372 --> 13:52.915
Hey, Frank.
Welcome back.

13:52.915 --> 13:54.417
I'll give you two
some time.

13:54.417 --> 13:56.043
Oh, thank you,
Carson.

13:56.043 --> 14:00.214
Oh, these are beautiful.
I'm so glad you're here.

14:00.214 --> 14:02.258
I was worried
when I didn't hear from you.

14:02.258 --> 14:04.344
I didn't write back
because I didn't think

14:04.344 --> 14:06.095
a letter would arrive
before I did,

14:06.095 --> 14:08.431
but nothing would keep me
from the wedding.

14:08.431 --> 14:10.308
They'll be thrilled
when they find out.

14:10.308 --> 14:12.560
And Cody is gonna be
so excited to see you.

14:12.560 --> 14:14.145
I can't wait
to see him too.

14:14.145 --> 14:16.147
Would you join us for dinner?

14:16.147 --> 14:17.691
Heh. Did you need to ask?

14:17.691 --> 14:19.609
[BOTH LAUGH]
Oh, Frank.

14:21.319 --> 14:24.280
[♪♪♪]

14:24.280 --> 14:25.824
All right,
now, listen up.

14:27.074 --> 14:28.117
In two minutes,

14:28.117 --> 14:29.494
I want you to start shooting

14:29.494 --> 14:31.412
out of each one
of these two windows,

14:31.412 --> 14:33.080
but aim
for the treetops.

14:33.080 --> 14:34.374
I got it.

14:45.385 --> 14:47.428
[DOORS CREAKING]

15:04.320 --> 15:06.406
[GUNSHOTS CONTINUE]

15:24.048 --> 15:26.300
WADE:
Harry? You okay?

15:27.552 --> 15:29.721
He's all tied up
at the moment.

15:35.268 --> 15:37.771
I love our walks.

15:37.771 --> 15:40.815
It's so nice to have
some alone time together.

15:42.108 --> 15:44.527
How're things going
on your side of the aisle?

15:44.527 --> 15:47.405
I couldn't ask for better
matrons of honor.

15:47.405 --> 15:49.741
Abigail always knows
what to say,

15:49.741 --> 15:51.951
and Rosemary...

15:51.951 --> 15:53.244
[CHUCKLES]

15:53.244 --> 15:55.079
Well, she tests
my limits,

15:55.079 --> 15:56.873
but I couldn't
do it without her.

15:56.873 --> 15:58.875
I'm really happy
Julie's here.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.209
Tom too.

16:00.209 --> 16:01.753
It wouldn't
be the same without

16:01.753 --> 16:03.546
at least some
of our family here.

16:04.714 --> 16:06.633
Have you seen Bill
yet this evening?

16:06.633 --> 16:08.968
Is he back?
Back from where?

16:08.968 --> 16:11.304
He didn't tell me
where he was going.

16:11.304 --> 16:13.097
Do you know?

16:13.097 --> 16:15.308
There was some Mountie
business out of town,

16:15.308 --> 16:17.811
and he went to
take care of it for you.

16:17.811 --> 16:19.479
That was
really nice of him.

16:19.479 --> 16:22.774
Mm-hmm.
[CHUCKLES]

16:22.774 --> 16:24.943
Okay, everyone,
so we're gonna rehearse this.

16:24.943 --> 16:26.402
When Opal
and Philip walk in,

16:26.402 --> 16:28.070
that's when
we light the candles.

16:28.070 --> 16:29.989
So everyone
in position.

16:36.621 --> 16:38.372
Begin.

16:39.039 --> 16:41.208
[♪♪♪]

16:41.208 --> 16:42.627
Not so fast, Opal.

16:42.627 --> 16:44.044
Go from the beginning.

16:49.550 --> 16:50.844
OPAL:
Like this?

16:50.844 --> 16:53.137
Just like that.

16:55.389 --> 16:57.099
Is that one too tall for you?

16:57.099 --> 16:58.351
No, I got it.

16:58.351 --> 17:00.394
Here,
let me help you.

17:05.149 --> 17:06.275
[GASPS]
Oh!

17:07.360 --> 17:09.821
BOY: Oh, no.
GIRL: Oh, no.

17:09.821 --> 17:11.906
[CHILDREN GASPING]

17:16.076 --> 17:19.038
Everyone has gone
above and beyond.

17:19.038 --> 17:21.081
Mm.
Doing what they can

17:21.081 --> 17:24.669
to make this wedding
go off without a hitch.

17:24.669 --> 17:26.004
Here's to
a smooth wedding.

17:26.004 --> 17:27.755
GIRL:
Help! Someone, help!

17:27.755 --> 17:30.383
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

17:30.383 --> 17:31.592
[GASPS]

17:31.592 --> 17:33.970
[FIRE CRACKLING]

17:33.970 --> 17:36.305
Is anyone inside?

17:36.305 --> 17:38.349
Opal!
Where's Opal?

17:38.349 --> 17:40.184
Are you all right?
Yes? Yes?

17:40.184 --> 17:43.229
We need to form a bucket brigade
from the pond to the church!

17:43.229 --> 17:45.356
Go back!
Get more men, more buckets!

17:45.356 --> 17:47.149
Are you okay? Yes?

17:47.149 --> 17:48.735
Where's
Mountie Jack?

17:48.735 --> 17:50.987
He went inside
to get Opal.

17:52.154 --> 17:54.073
Oh!
No, no, no! Elizabeth, wait!

17:54.073 --> 17:55.157
No! Too dangerous.

17:56.743 --> 17:58.786
[♪♪♪]

17:58.786 --> 18:00.955
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

18:02.289 --> 18:04.250
[GASPS, SIGHS]
Oh, jeez.

18:04.250 --> 18:07.003
Here. Give her to me.
I'll take her.

18:08.421 --> 18:10.798
Go-- go with him.
I'll stay here and help. Lee!

18:10.798 --> 18:12.508
Okay.
Let's go. Let's go.

18:16.846 --> 18:19.265
Come on, everyone,
hurry up!

18:27.189 --> 18:29.191
CARSON:
She was overcome
by smoke,

18:29.191 --> 18:31.611
but she'll be okay.

18:31.611 --> 18:33.279
I sent her parents home.

18:33.279 --> 18:34.280
You should go too.

18:34.280 --> 18:36.074
OPAL:
Hi, Miss Thatcher.

18:38.158 --> 18:40.078
Hi.

18:40.078 --> 18:42.288
[♪♪♪]

18:44.791 --> 18:46.667
How are you feeling?

18:46.667 --> 18:47.961
Okay.

18:47.961 --> 18:49.253
Did I miss the wedding?

18:49.253 --> 18:52.548
No, sweetie.
You didn't miss a thing.

18:52.548 --> 18:55.760
Do I still get to be
your flower girl?

18:57.011 --> 18:59.138
Let's see how you're feeling,
all right?

19:00.473 --> 19:02.642
But, for now...

19:02.642 --> 19:04.978
you've got to rest.

19:15.113 --> 19:16.614
I'm sorry,
Miss Thatcher.

19:16.614 --> 19:17.657
It was all my fault.

19:17.657 --> 19:19.199
No, it wasn't.
It was my fault.

19:19.199 --> 19:20.367
It was an accident.

19:20.367 --> 19:22.036
We ruined everything,
didn't we?

19:22.036 --> 19:24.122
No, you didn't.
Really.

19:24.122 --> 19:26.666
You and Cody and the others,
you just--

19:27.875 --> 19:29.627
You cared about
our wedding so much

19:29.627 --> 19:31.587
that you wanted it
to be perfect.

19:31.587 --> 19:32.755
I understand that.

19:35.133 --> 19:37.343
[♪♪♪]

19:52.274 --> 19:53.442
JACK:
How's Opal?

19:53.442 --> 19:55.194
She's gonna be fine.

19:55.194 --> 19:56.612
Thank God.

19:58.364 --> 20:00.700
JACK:
There's a lot of damage.

20:03.494 --> 20:04.787
My wedding dress...

20:04.787 --> 20:05.872
[SIGHS]

20:05.872 --> 20:07.665
[♪♪♪]

20:07.665 --> 20:09.083
I'm so sorry.

20:09.083 --> 20:11.251
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

20:12.003 --> 20:13.546
Elizabeth...

20:13.546 --> 20:15.589
we can either
postpone the wedding

20:15.589 --> 20:17.925
or we'll have
the ceremony outside,

20:17.925 --> 20:19.886
with the clothes
on our back.

20:19.886 --> 20:20.970
No.

20:22.555 --> 20:24.098
We have a day
and a night.

20:24.098 --> 20:25.265
To do what?

20:25.265 --> 20:27.393
To make
everything right.

20:27.393 --> 20:30.146
We can't rebuild
a wedding dress in a day.

20:30.146 --> 20:31.230
And a night.

20:33.816 --> 20:37.153
Well, it wouldn't
be easy.

20:37.153 --> 20:39.030
With all those
decorations--

20:39.030 --> 20:41.323
Yes, but if
we all pitch in.

20:42.366 --> 20:43.951
Whatever we need
for the dress,

20:43.951 --> 20:45.203
I'll donate
from my shop.

20:45.203 --> 20:46.620
NED:
Whatever else we need,

20:46.620 --> 20:48.706
if my mercantile's got it,
you can have it.

20:48.706 --> 20:51.125
LEE:
And the walls are still intact,
pretty much.

20:51.125 --> 20:52.334
A little
elbow grease--

20:52.334 --> 20:54.378
Yeah, a fresh coat
of paint.

20:55.213 --> 20:56.463
What are we waiting for?

20:56.463 --> 20:58.424
Abigail, it's just
too much to ask.

20:58.424 --> 20:59.884
No. You didn't ask.

20:59.884 --> 21:02.302
We're volunteering.

21:05.890 --> 21:08.101
[ALL LAUGH]

21:09.185 --> 21:10.811
ABIGAIL:
Oh, gentlemen. Thank you.

21:10.811 --> 21:12.897
The sewing machines
can go right here.

21:12.897 --> 21:16.025
ROSEMARY:
Okay, so I'll need you three
on the sewing machines.

21:16.025 --> 21:18.236
Clara, you and I can cut.

21:18.236 --> 21:20.404
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

21:22.156 --> 21:24.366
[♪♪♪]

21:31.082 --> 21:32.166
Father!

21:32.166 --> 21:34.961
Hello, my dear.

21:34.961 --> 21:36.796
[SIGHS]

21:36.796 --> 21:38.881
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

21:38.881 --> 21:41.092
What's happened?

21:41.592 --> 21:44.011
[SIGHS]

21:44.011 --> 21:47.056
So the wagon with the paint
and supplies will be here soon.

21:47.056 --> 21:48.724
Good, we're gonna need it.

21:48.724 --> 21:50.143
Who's that?

21:52.270 --> 21:53.980
That's my future
father-in-law.

21:53.980 --> 21:55.982
Mr. Thatcher.

21:55.982 --> 21:57.733
Hello, Jack.
I just arrived.

21:57.733 --> 21:59.318
Elizabeth told me
about the fire.

21:59.318 --> 22:01.445
Everyone's working hard
to get it repaired.

22:01.445 --> 22:03.572
All these men?
Must be costing a fortune.

22:03.572 --> 22:05.241
Actually,
they're volunteers.

22:05.241 --> 22:06.784
Really?

22:07.451 --> 22:08.828
How industrious.

22:08.828 --> 22:11.080
We like to think of it
as being neighborly.

22:11.080 --> 22:13.624
Well, I'm not a neighbor.

22:13.624 --> 22:16.043
But I'm family,
so let me help out.

22:17.670 --> 22:19.046
Yes, sir.

22:19.046 --> 22:21.257
[♪♪♪]

22:25.052 --> 22:28.181
Uh, just up on that wall,
please.

22:32.685 --> 22:34.812
[WOMEN MURMURING
INDISTINCTLY]

22:54.498 --> 22:57.626
So you, uh, got
any jitters about tomorrow?

22:57.626 --> 22:59.670
Not really.

23:00.754 --> 23:01.755
Okay, maybe a few.

23:01.755 --> 23:03.381
[CHUCKLES]

23:04.633 --> 23:07.553
Well, if I'm completely
honest, Lee...

23:09.096 --> 23:11.473
I'm shaking in my boots.
Of course you are.

23:11.473 --> 23:14.601
Just like I was
right before I married Rosie.

23:14.601 --> 23:16.603
No. No, you didn't
seem like it.

23:16.603 --> 23:18.314
Are you kidding me?
I was a wreck.

23:18.314 --> 23:19.690
I was convinced
I was gonna

23:19.690 --> 23:21.608
mess up my vows,
make a fool of myself.

23:21.608 --> 23:22.651
Convinced.

23:22.651 --> 23:23.610
You didn't.

23:23.610 --> 23:25.071
No. And neither will you.

23:26.280 --> 23:28.949
Just gotta forget
about the ceremony,

23:28.949 --> 23:30.910
forget about the guests,

23:30.910 --> 23:32.912
just think about
your bride-to-be.

23:32.912 --> 23:37.041
This is the day you finally
become man and wife, forever.

23:37.041 --> 23:39.585
So you say the vows,
and you put

23:39.585 --> 23:42.046
the rings on each other's
fingers, and that's it.

23:42.046 --> 23:44.131
You're done.

23:44.131 --> 23:46.008
You're a good friend, Lee.

23:46.008 --> 23:47.718
Yeah, I know.

23:47.718 --> 23:49.387
So are you,
and you're gonna

23:49.387 --> 23:51.389
make a great husband
to Elizabeth,

23:51.389 --> 23:53.933
in...about 14 hours.

23:55.517 --> 23:56.602
Fourteen hours?

23:56.602 --> 23:58.520
Fourteen hours.

23:59.063 --> 24:02.108
[♪♪♪]

24:02.108 --> 24:03.609
Here you go.

24:03.609 --> 24:04.902
For the bodice.

24:04.902 --> 24:06.987
[GASPS]
Oh, Faith.

24:06.987 --> 24:09.323
I tried to follow your design
as best I could.

24:09.323 --> 24:12.993
Oh, well, the attention
to detail is just...

24:12.993 --> 24:14.870
Well, it's stunning.

24:14.870 --> 24:16.956
Guess it comes
with being a nurse.

24:16.956 --> 24:19.166
[♪♪♪]

24:37.935 --> 24:39.645
CLARA:
Just what I was afraid of.

24:39.645 --> 24:41.021
There isn't
enough lace left

24:41.021 --> 24:42.815
to make the whole dress
over again.

24:42.815 --> 24:44.566
[MUTTERS
INDISTINCTLY]

24:44.566 --> 24:47.736
Hmm?
What was that?

24:47.736 --> 24:49.905
Mm! Thank you.

24:49.905 --> 24:51.031
We can use my dress.

24:51.031 --> 24:52.574
My dress was lace.

24:52.574 --> 24:54.910
We can deconstruct my dress
to make Elizabeth's.

24:54.910 --> 24:56.287
ABIGAIL:
That's a great idea.

24:56.287 --> 24:58.122
Hello.
How's it all going?

24:58.122 --> 24:59.290
It's coming
along great.

24:59.290 --> 25:01.208
It still needs work,
but don't worry.

25:02.751 --> 25:04.502
I have another dress
I can wear.

25:04.502 --> 25:06.422
I don't want you
to exhaust yourselves

25:06.422 --> 25:07.881
trying to pull off a miracle.

25:07.881 --> 25:10.468
Well, lucky for you,
we specialize in miracles.

25:10.468 --> 25:12.552
ROSEMARY:
Elizabeth...

25:12.552 --> 25:16.265
when Jack catches sight of you
walking down the aisle,

25:16.265 --> 25:18.100
he's going to think
he's in heaven.

25:19.226 --> 25:20.269
Now scoot.

25:20.269 --> 25:22.938
Oh.
We have some work to do.

25:22.938 --> 25:25.565
[WOMEN SIGH,
CHATTER INDISTINCTLY]

25:25.565 --> 25:27.776
[♪♪♪]

25:30.737 --> 25:32.739
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

25:34.950 --> 25:37.161
[♪♪♪]

25:38.287 --> 25:40.538
[KNOCKS]

25:43.125 --> 25:44.335
Father.

25:44.335 --> 25:47.254
Hello.
Hello.

25:50.174 --> 25:51.633
[SIGHS]

25:51.633 --> 25:53.135
This is home.

25:53.135 --> 25:54.970
Mm-hmm.

25:54.970 --> 25:56.930
Come on in.

25:58.307 --> 25:59.599
How are you holding up?

26:01.143 --> 26:02.436
[EXHALES HEAVILY]
Oh.

26:02.436 --> 26:04.188
Excited.

26:04.188 --> 26:05.523
Nervous.

26:07.358 --> 26:08.650
[CHUCKLES]

26:08.650 --> 26:10.277
Don't be.

26:10.277 --> 26:13.906
You're marrying a good man,
and he's devoted to you.

26:13.906 --> 26:16.283
[SIGHS]

26:16.283 --> 26:18.244
You have no idea
how long I've waited

26:18.244 --> 26:19.370
to hear that from you.

26:19.370 --> 26:21.872
[CHUCKLES]

26:21.872 --> 26:23.957
Your mother...

26:23.957 --> 26:26.544
asked me
to give this to you.

26:30.214 --> 26:31.673
Oh...

26:31.673 --> 26:34.468
She wants you to wear this
on your wedding day,

26:34.468 --> 26:37.179
just like
she did on ours.

26:37.179 --> 26:39.973
[♪♪♪]

26:39.973 --> 26:43.185
I see so much of
your mother in you.

26:46.355 --> 26:48.648
I take that as
the highest compliment.

26:48.648 --> 26:49.942
To both of you.

26:55.406 --> 26:56.490
What is it?

26:57.533 --> 27:00.286
[LAUGHS]

27:00.286 --> 27:02.496
I remember holding you
as a little girl.

27:02.496 --> 27:04.540
When I'd get home,
you would run up to me

27:04.540 --> 27:07.543
and throw your little arms
around me and hold me tight.

27:07.543 --> 27:10.712
That's about as good
as it gets for a father.

27:11.713 --> 27:13.048
But now...

27:13.048 --> 27:14.883
you're a grown woman,

27:14.883 --> 27:16.009
moving on.

27:16.009 --> 27:17.803
Oh, Father.

27:17.803 --> 27:19.721
I may be grown,

27:19.721 --> 27:21.807
but I will always be
your little girl.

27:32.859 --> 27:34.528
ROSEMARY:
Clara is putting

27:34.528 --> 27:36.863
the finishing touches
on your dress right now.

27:36.863 --> 27:40.493
I can't believe I'm about
to be a married woman.

27:40.493 --> 27:42.660
The day has finally arrived.

27:42.660 --> 27:45.331
And we're here to give you
all the wedded-bliss

27:45.331 --> 27:47.916
advice you'll need.
Which is pretty simple, really.

27:47.916 --> 27:50.794
It's all about love,
kindness, and devotion.

27:50.794 --> 27:52.712
And honesty
with your husband.

27:52.712 --> 27:56.467
Lee and I always talk about
everything that's on our minds.

27:56.467 --> 27:58.093
I do most of the talking,

27:58.093 --> 27:59.970
but Lee is
an excellent listener.

27:59.970 --> 28:01.347
Most of the time.

28:01.347 --> 28:04.016
And it's okay
if you and Jack disagree.

28:04.016 --> 28:06.893
You don't have to have the same
opinion about everything.

28:06.893 --> 28:08.312
It's okay to make mistakes.

28:08.312 --> 28:09.938
Lee makes most of them,

28:09.938 --> 28:11.565
but I always forgive him,

28:11.565 --> 28:13.317
because nobody's perfect.

28:14.026 --> 28:15.486
Nobody.

28:16.612 --> 28:17.988
Even me.

28:17.988 --> 28:20.032
Occasionally.

28:20.032 --> 28:21.241
[ALL LAUGH]

28:21.241 --> 28:22.742
But most of all,
Elizabeth,

28:22.742 --> 28:24.953
as a married couple,

28:24.953 --> 28:27.373
you'll be sharing
your lives together,

28:27.373 --> 28:28.999
which means sharing your heart.

28:30.000 --> 28:32.628
Love conquers all.

28:32.628 --> 28:34.004
Truly.

28:37.508 --> 28:39.426
I just love you both
so much.

28:39.426 --> 28:41.094
We love you too.

28:41.094 --> 28:43.930
Well, we better get started
on your hair.

28:43.930 --> 28:44.931
Mm-hmm!

28:44.931 --> 28:47.017
[GIGGLING]

28:51.271 --> 28:52.272
[SIGHS]

28:52.272 --> 28:54.400
What's wrong?

28:54.400 --> 28:57.903
Bill's gone out of town on
Mountie business. He's not back.

28:57.903 --> 28:58.945
Hope he's okay.

28:58.945 --> 29:01.073
I'm sure
he just got delayed.

29:01.073 --> 29:04.493
You've got a wedding
to focus on.

29:04.493 --> 29:05.827
Right.

29:05.827 --> 29:06.912
How do I look?

29:08.205 --> 29:09.665
Dad'd be so proud of you.

29:09.665 --> 29:11.875
[♪♪♪]

29:14.086 --> 29:16.004
I hope so.

29:18.382 --> 29:21.427
You're a Mountie,
just like him.

29:21.427 --> 29:24.054
And...

29:24.054 --> 29:25.681
you found a great woman

29:25.681 --> 29:28.016
to spend the rest
of your life with.

29:30.519 --> 29:32.896
He would've been
proud of you too, Tom.

29:32.896 --> 29:34.856
You're gonna be
a captain of industry.

29:34.856 --> 29:37.526
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

29:37.526 --> 29:38.527
About time to go?

29:38.527 --> 29:39.570
Yeah.

29:41.447 --> 29:42.489
The rings.

29:42.489 --> 29:43.574
What about them?

29:43.574 --> 29:45.117
I gave them to Bill.

29:46.910 --> 29:49.121
[♪♪♪]

29:50.956 --> 29:52.249
Something must've happened.

29:52.249 --> 29:53.833
I'm sure
he's just delayed.

29:53.833 --> 29:55.210
What are we gonna do?

29:55.210 --> 29:57.463
[SIGHING]
I don't know.

29:57.463 --> 29:58.797
[INHALES SHARPLY]

29:58.797 --> 29:59.965
I have an idea.

29:59.965 --> 30:01.258
I'll be right back.

30:01.258 --> 30:03.260
I need my basket of petals.

30:03.260 --> 30:05.804
I'll give it to you before
we start down the aisle.

30:05.804 --> 30:08.265
Miss Thatcher?
Just a moment, Philip.

30:08.265 --> 30:09.933
Cody, Ruby,
you can go now,

30:09.933 --> 30:12.894
but no lighting candles
until we say it's okay. Go.

30:12.894 --> 30:14.772
Ushers, people will be
arriving soon.

30:14.772 --> 30:16.523
Go take your places
in the church

30:16.523 --> 30:17.941
and show them to their seats.

30:17.941 --> 30:19.359
Miss Thatcher!
Timmy,

30:19.359 --> 30:21.570
do you have your music
for the wedding march?

30:21.570 --> 30:24.030
Right here.
Go ahead.

30:24.030 --> 30:26.325
Miss Thatcher.
Oh, yes, Philip. What is it?

30:26.325 --> 30:27.576
Where are the rings?

30:30.162 --> 30:31.955
Where are the rings?

30:31.955 --> 30:33.582
Rosie, I need
your wedding band.

30:33.582 --> 30:35.083
What? Why?

30:35.083 --> 30:36.251
Bill hasn't shown up yet.

30:36.251 --> 30:37.670
Jack and Elizabeth
need ours.

30:37.670 --> 30:39.338
Looking for these?
Where have you been?

30:39.338 --> 30:41.089
LEE:
Yes! Yes.

30:41.089 --> 30:42.841
Here you go.
Thank you.

30:42.841 --> 30:44.884
Your suit is in the jail.
Hurry up.

30:44.884 --> 30:46.303
I guess
I'd better go change.

30:46.303 --> 30:48.430
Word has it
there's a wedding. Ladies.

30:48.430 --> 30:50.349
Oh, aren't weddings exciting?

30:50.349 --> 30:52.392
[♪♪♪]

30:52.392 --> 30:54.019
You two look lovely.

30:54.019 --> 30:55.771
Thank you.
Thank you.

30:55.771 --> 30:57.022
[ROSEMARY CHUCKLES]

30:57.022 --> 30:59.191
There. Something blue.

30:59.191 --> 31:01.109
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

31:01.109 --> 31:03.320
[♪♪♪]

31:08.241 --> 31:09.909
You okay?

31:13.622 --> 31:15.708
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

31:17.501 --> 31:19.169
[SIGHS]

31:19.169 --> 31:21.213
Gentlemen, I have it
on good authority

31:21.213 --> 31:23.298
that the bride
has arrived.

31:23.298 --> 31:24.924
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

31:26.218 --> 31:27.594
Glad you could
make it.

31:27.594 --> 31:28.637
You and me both.

31:28.637 --> 31:30.222
Here.
This is for you.

31:30.222 --> 31:33.600
Thanks.
What is that smell?

31:33.600 --> 31:36.645
It's a root cellar.
Don't ask.

31:36.645 --> 31:38.146
Okay.

31:38.146 --> 31:39.939
We're five minutes
behind schedule.

31:39.939 --> 31:42.860
It's fine.
Fashionably late.

31:43.985 --> 31:45.696
She's here.

31:45.696 --> 31:47.906
[♪♪♪]

31:49.115 --> 31:50.367
When the curtains open,

31:50.367 --> 31:52.411
you start down
the aisle.

32:02.421 --> 32:04.506
[PLAYING "WEDDING MARCH"
BY MENDELSSOHN]

32:36.789 --> 32:37.831
[WHISPERS]
Well done.

32:37.831 --> 32:40.542
[WHISPERS]
Good job.

32:58.560 --> 33:00.771
[♪♪♪]

33:09.696 --> 33:11.698
[WAGNER'S "BRIDAL CHORUS"
PLAYING]

33:11.698 --> 33:13.909
[♪♪♪]

33:42.228 --> 33:44.439
FRANK:
Friends, we're
gathered here today

33:44.439 --> 33:47.108
to witness the joining
of this man and this woman

33:47.108 --> 33:48.694
in holy matrimony.

33:48.694 --> 33:50.654
For everything,
there is a season,

33:50.654 --> 33:53.031
and a time for
every purpose under heaven.

33:53.031 --> 33:55.868
Love is patient, love is kind.

33:55.868 --> 33:57.744
JACK:
Elizabeth...

33:57.744 --> 33:59.955
[♪♪♪]

34:01.832 --> 34:04.083
I choose you
and no other.

34:05.293 --> 34:07.170
Your happiness
is the only question

34:07.170 --> 34:09.047
I want to spend
my life answering.

34:10.215 --> 34:11.591
Your heart is the only flame

34:11.591 --> 34:14.177
I will endeavor to
keep alight.

34:14.177 --> 34:17.138
Before you said yes
to marrying me,

34:17.138 --> 34:19.391
I was already yours
in every way.

34:23.228 --> 34:26.272
So I marry you today

34:26.272 --> 34:27.733
without hesitation

34:27.733 --> 34:28.817
or doubt.

34:30.485 --> 34:34.113
I'm committed to you...
absolutely.

34:35.281 --> 34:38.243
I love you with
everything that I am.

34:39.118 --> 34:40.453
Forever.

34:46.919 --> 34:48.712
Jack...

34:48.712 --> 34:50.756
[♪♪♪]

34:50.756 --> 34:55.134
I never expected to find love
when I came to Coal Valley.

34:55.134 --> 34:57.178
But somewhere along the way,

34:57.178 --> 35:00.766
without even realizing
it was happening,

35:00.766 --> 35:04.352
you became the most
important person in my life.

35:07.064 --> 35:09.691
You're my shoulder to cry on...

35:09.691 --> 35:13.278
my favorite to dream with...

35:13.278 --> 35:15.196
and my greatest surprise.

35:16.489 --> 35:18.867
I'd offer you my heart,

35:18.867 --> 35:22.203
but the truth is, you've
had it for quite some time now.

35:24.414 --> 35:25.540
So instead...

35:25.540 --> 35:28.376
I'm gonna
give you my soul.

35:30.879 --> 35:33.924
I love you, Jack Thornton...

35:34.967 --> 35:37.302
...from chalk dust
to eternity.

35:37.302 --> 35:39.554
[ALL LAUGH]

35:41.556 --> 35:43.600
I'm yours.

35:46.895 --> 35:49.188
We're ready for the rings.

35:53.276 --> 35:55.028
Thank you.

35:55.028 --> 35:57.072
[♪♪♪]

36:02.368 --> 36:04.203
I give you this ring

36:04.203 --> 36:06.706
as a symbol of my love.

36:08.667 --> 36:10.585
With all that I am,

36:10.585 --> 36:12.671
and all that I have,

36:12.671 --> 36:13.922
I honor you.

36:19.052 --> 36:21.138
With this ring...

36:22.097 --> 36:24.057
...I thee wed.

36:24.057 --> 36:25.767
[BOTH LAUGH]

36:25.767 --> 36:27.644
Elizabeth...Jack...

36:28.603 --> 36:30.022
it is my great pleasure

36:30.022 --> 36:31.481
to now pronounce you

36:31.481 --> 36:33.025
husband and wife.

36:33.025 --> 36:34.400
Jack...

36:34.400 --> 36:35.652
you may kiss your--

36:35.652 --> 36:37.029
...bride.

36:37.029 --> 36:38.155
[ALL LAUGH]

36:38.155 --> 36:40.532
[APPLAUDING, CHEERING]

36:42.492 --> 36:44.703
[♪♪♪]

37:13.982 --> 37:15.942
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

37:15.942 --> 37:17.944
[♪♪♪]

37:17.944 --> 37:20.446
JACK: Thank you.
ELIZABETH: Thank you so much.

37:20.446 --> 37:23.033
Oh, Elizabeth,

37:23.033 --> 37:26.327
you really are the most
beautiful bride I've ever seen.

37:26.327 --> 37:28.663
Thank you. It's because of
this beautiful dress,

37:28.663 --> 37:30.123
thanks to you
and the women.

37:30.123 --> 37:31.499
Oh...

37:31.499 --> 37:33.919
Congratulations.
Thank you.

37:36.838 --> 37:38.798
Thank you.
Mm.

37:40.050 --> 37:42.094
Congratulations
to you both.

37:42.094 --> 37:44.345
Jack, you are
one lucky man.

37:44.345 --> 37:46.305
Don't I know it.

37:49.392 --> 37:50.894
I must admit,

37:50.894 --> 37:52.104
we did a wonderful job

37:52.104 --> 37:53.563
pulling this all off.

37:53.563 --> 37:55.023
We certainly did.

37:55.023 --> 37:57.567
[CHUCKLES] Cheers.
Cheers.

37:58.860 --> 38:00.528
Um...

38:00.528 --> 38:02.739
I'm having an art show
in Hamilton,

38:02.739 --> 38:04.241
in a few months.

38:04.241 --> 38:06.325
Maybe you could
come by and see it.

38:07.786 --> 38:09.662
Maybe I can.

38:11.081 --> 38:12.749
LEE:
Uh, excuse me, everyone?

38:12.749 --> 38:14.876
Can I have your attention
for a minute?

38:14.876 --> 38:19.131
Um, the other best man would
like to say a few words, so...

38:19.131 --> 38:21.716
The one who almost
didn't make it.

38:21.716 --> 38:23.301
[ALL LAUGH]

38:23.301 --> 38:24.761
BILL:
I'll keep this short.

38:24.761 --> 38:27.180
Jack...

38:27.180 --> 38:29.224
you fight the good fight,
my friend.

38:29.224 --> 38:31.977
You protect the community.

38:31.977 --> 38:34.187
You deserve the very best.

38:34.187 --> 38:36.439
Luckily,
you found it in Elizabeth.

38:37.607 --> 38:39.109
To the bride
and the groom...

38:39.109 --> 38:41.360
may they always be as happy
as they are today.

38:41.360 --> 38:42.654
ALL:
Hear, hear!

38:42.654 --> 38:44.322
To the bride and groom.
Hear, hear.

38:44.322 --> 38:45.991
ALL:
Hear, hear.

38:45.991 --> 38:47.951
[SPOON CLINKING ON GLASS]

38:47.951 --> 38:50.745
I would like to just
say a few words.

38:50.745 --> 38:52.872
I've had the great honor

38:52.872 --> 38:55.834
of watching this romance
blossom into a love story.

38:55.834 --> 38:58.336
And the sparks
were certainly flying

38:58.336 --> 39:00.379
when Jack Thornton
and Elizabeth Thatcher

39:00.379 --> 39:02.048
first laid eyes on each other.

39:02.048 --> 39:03.341
[ALL LAUGH]

39:03.341 --> 39:04.968
ABIGAIL:
There was no denying

39:04.968 --> 39:08.680
that something special
was unfolding before my eyes.

39:09.181 --> 39:10.640
Love.

39:10.640 --> 39:13.268
A love that doesn't
come along every day.

39:14.352 --> 39:15.770
A love that...

39:17.438 --> 39:19.274
is undeniable.

39:19.274 --> 39:21.067
A love that can't be broken...

39:21.943 --> 39:24.737
and that will endure.

39:24.737 --> 39:28.950
A love that lifetimes
are built upon.

39:28.950 --> 39:32.204
To Mr. and Mrs. Jack Thornton.

39:32.204 --> 39:35.248
May God bless you
and keep you.

39:35.248 --> 39:37.583
Congratulations
to the newlyweds.

39:37.583 --> 39:39.669
[ALL RESPOND INDISTINCTLY]

39:47.385 --> 39:49.137
Oh, Elizabeth.

39:49.137 --> 39:50.805
I think it's time

39:50.805 --> 39:54.142
for the bride and her father
to have their first dance.

39:55.518 --> 39:57.812
Thank you.

39:57.812 --> 39:59.898
[PIANO SONG PLAYING]

40:01.774 --> 40:02.984
I remember
when we'd dance

40:02.984 --> 40:05.444
with your feet
on top of mine.

40:05.444 --> 40:07.655
I don't think you'd want me
to do that now.

40:07.655 --> 40:08.781
[LAUGHS]

40:22.712 --> 40:23.963
May I?

40:31.721 --> 40:33.556
Finally.

40:33.556 --> 40:35.350
Finally.

40:35.350 --> 40:37.560
[♪♪♪]

40:46.111 --> 40:48.280
[PEOPLE CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY]

41:00.041 --> 41:01.960
Would you care
to dance?

41:01.960 --> 41:03.795
[LAUGHS]
Yes.

41:30.529 --> 41:32.740
[♪♪♪]
